Class GenericModule

java.lang.Object
  de.fu.weave.meta.GenericModule
All Implemented Interfaces:
Module
Direct Known Subclasses:
About, ErrorHandler, GenericCRUD, Sandbox, Start
public abstract class GenericModule
extends java.lang.Object
implements Module

Abstract base class for all Application modules.

A module is dynamically loaded at startup of a Controller. The modules to be loaded are specified in web.xml via “module:name_of_the_module”, where “name_of_the_module” is the name that the module itself has propagated via it’s ModuleName-Annotation. This is also the name by which a module is reffered by an HTTP request. See the about-Module for an example.

Author:
Julian Fleischer

put

public final org.w3c.dom.Element put(org.w3c.dom.Element parentElement,
                                     java.lang.Object value)
Appends an Object to an Element already assigned.

Since the object is translated to XML its name will be taken from the parent that the object is assigned to. The new element will be created within the XMLNS_ITEM-Namespace instead of XMLNS_DATA.

Parameters:
parentElement - The parent the new Element will be appended to
value - The object that is to be assigned.
Returns:
The newly created Element
